climbs.name: Low T
climbs.fa: Mark Grazier, Anna Brown & Karl Kiser Summer 2019

content.description: The crux, above the 5th bolt, is technical face climbing at the top of the route.
content.protection: 6 bolts to a bolt & chain anchor. It can be set by climbing left from the Gentle Touch anchor.
content.location: Start on Gentle Touch, traverse left at the second bolt and then continue up.

content.description: This is the direct start to Low T.  Grab a chock stone and go up and left on side pulls, the crux, to big holds.  Cross a ledge and continue on small face holds to the top.
content.protection: Bolt & chain anchor.  It can be set from climbing left from the Gentle Touch anchor.
content.location: Start on the left side of the west face of High Rock.

content.description: Climb the crack but trend right before the large ledge on Temp 1.  The crux is the traverse to a large handhold.  Continue upward to the anchor.
content.location: Start in the right to left crack on the east face.  This climb shares the start with Temp 1.

content.description: Climb the slanting crack, stand on a substantial ledge and the make several hard moves to reach a small left facing weakness.  Continue on up to the anchor on the left.
content.location: The start is on the east side of the formation.  Climb a right to left crack and then continue up and left to a shared anchor with Schedule 1.

content.description: The climb has a crux in the thin fingers section and the wide section at the top.  It may be harder if you cannot get inside the squeeze chimney.
content.protection: 2 bolts for the TR. It can be set from the top with caution.  Or one can climb left from the Low T anchor.
content.location: This is the crack on the north face of High Rock.

climbs.name: Schedule 2
climbs.fa: Mak Grazier, Anna Brown & Karl Kiser Summer 2019

content.description: The crux is off the ground above the first bolt.  Fun climbing but a little short.
content.protection: 3 bolts to a bolt and chain anchor.
content.location: The route goes up the small face to the right of the main buttress.

climbs.name: Schedule 1
climbs.fa: Mark Starr, Zoe Zou & Karl Kiser, summer 2019

content.description: Stem and side pull the edge, then hand traverse right below the fourth bolt, then find good holds above and right of the anchor to finish the route.  There is a variation going straight up to the anchors from the third bolt without the traverse.
content.protection: 4 bolts to a bolt and chain anchor.
content.location: Go around to the east side of High Rock, third class to a chimney on the left side.

climbs.name: Gentle Touch
climbs.fa: Karl Kiser, Mark Starr & Zoe Zou, summer 2019

content.description: This is a good moderate route.  Just stay on the right edge to the left of the chimney.
content.protection: 6 bolts to a bolt and chain anchor.  One low belay bolt on a large ledge.
content.location: The climb is on the right side of the west face of High Rock.

content.description: The rock sits, on the hill facing north, above the other small rocks of the left side.
